cs.SE, cs.SD, cs.PL, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper discusses software development methodologies and evaluates them based on criteria related to product quality and adherence to agile practices. This falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper explores specific practices and their strengths and weaknesses, which could fall under software development (cs.SD) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses technical debt, which could fall under cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
